6 Section 2. KRS 247.220 is amended to read as follows:
7 (1) The Commissioner of Agriculture shall make grants of state funds to qualified local
8 agricultural fairs on a matching basis, to be used by them to pay premium awards
9 for exhibits and displays of domestic livestock, poultry, harness horse racing, other
10 horse events, and agricultural products. The premiums actually awarded shall
11 conform to those appearing on the premium list issued by the fair.
12 (2) The state may provide funds for use in the establishment of new facilities and
13 improvement of existing facilities for use in conducting events at local agricultural
14 fairs as provided by this section. No grant for buildings shall be made until the local
15 fair board has complied with the local fair program and qualified for the state grant
16 as provided in subsection (5) of this section. Grants for facilities shall be made
17 under regulations promulgated by the Fair Council and the Commissioner of
18 Agriculture. In no event shall the allocation for facilities result in a decrease in the
19 number of approved agricultural classes or premiums.
20 (3) There shall be a Fair Council in the Department of Agriculture. The council shall
21 act in an advisory capacity to the Commissioner in all matters pertaining to the
22 administration of the department's fair program. It shall be called into session when
23 there are matters for its consideration. It shall meet at least twice each calendar year
24 at Frankfort or at any other place that may be determined.
25 (4) (a) The council shall be composed of:
26 1. The Commissioner, or the Commissioner's designee, as
27 chair[chairman];
