16 of the council, appoint additional members to the council.
17 (5) To qualify for a grant of state funds, a fair shall meet standards set by the
18 Commissioner and his advisory council whose approval may be given only if the
19 fair:
20 (a) Provides in its bylaws for holding an annual fair running for at least three (3)
21 days;
22 (b) Presents, through the medium of youth organizations such as 4-H clubs,
23 Future Farmers of America, and other similar organizations, an educational
24 program concerning the production and marketing of the livestock, poultry,
25 and horse industries;
26 (c) Complies with all administrative regulations which the Department of
27 Agriculture is hereby authorized to promulgate; and
