1 (d) Appoints one (1) or more members to its fair board from local livestock
2 associations, horsemen's associations, and county farm bureaus, and selects
3 one (1) or more county extension agents and vocational agriculture teachers
4 for counties served by the fair as members of the board. Wherever local
5 livestock associations, horsemen's associations, and farm bureaus are in
6 existence, appointees are to be nominated to the fair board by these
7 organizations. Where fairs serve an area, appointments may be made from all
8 counties within the particular area. It shall be the responsibility of the
9 appointees to aid in establishing premium lists and planning agricultural
10 exhibits.
11 (6) Any fair receiving a grant of state funds shall file with the director of the
12 Livestock[Shows and Fairs] Division in the Department of Agriculture, by
13 December 1 of the year in which the grant is received, satisfactory proof that all
14 state premium awards have been paid and a certified notarized financial report
15 submitted by the treasurer of the local fair association.
16 Section 3. Whereas agriculture is a vital and integral component to the
17 economy, and farm families throughout the Commonwealth depend on the expansion and
18 success of a flourishing agricultural industry, an emergency is declared to exist, and this
19 Act takes effect upon its passage and approval by the Governor or upon its otherwise
20 becoming a law.
